page.title: 19EDGEHEAD
page.content:
THE VILLAGE OF EDGEHEAD RUNS NORTH TO SOUTH AND CONSISTS OF 60 HOUSES. THERE IS ONE SCHOOL, ONE BUILDERS MERCHANT AND NO SHOPS. IT IS A DESIRABLE RESIDENTIAL AREA FOR CITY COMMUTERS. THE POPULATION OF EDGEHEAD IS APPROXIMATELY 180. THE HOUSING APPEARS TO HAVE DEVELOPED IN THREE SEPARATE STAGES :
THOSE BUILT OVER 100 YEARS AGO WHICH ARE ON EITHER SIDE OF THE MAIN STREET. THOSE BUILT 15-20 YEARS AGO WHICH ARE ON THE SOUTHSIDE OF THE VILLAGE. THOSE BUILT AS PART OF A NEW DEVELOPMENT IN RECENT YEARS OCCUPYING A SITE JUST OFF THE MAIN STREET AT THE NORTH OF THE VILLAGE OVERLOOKING THE PLAYING FIELDS. THERE IS ALSO A LARGE UNUSED AREA OF LAND WHICH MAY BE USED IN THE FUTURE.
